    "Lastly, n represents the noise added to the image.",
    "In the SISR task, a single low-resolution image might correspond to multiple high-resolution images, presenting an ill-posed problem.",
    "Initially, using L1 or L2 loss during training frequently led to blurred predictions despite yielding higher PSNR metrics.",
    "This approach leans toward average losses, inadequately addressing uncertainty in super-resolution problems, resulting in a notable decrease in high-frequency details.",
    "Recently, leveraging (11) VGG-19's 26, 34, 35 style and content losses has demonstrated the ability to generate more explicit images and improve visual quality, notably assisting in restoring high-frequency details."
